    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to a type of still life that features smokers' accoutrements such as tobacco pipes, smoldering hemp wicks, and braziers of burning coals. Jugs of beer or glasses of wine are also typically depicted. The term tabakje is translated from the Dutch as "little tobacco."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046913/Albany Institute of History and Art [online] (n.d.)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指稱一種以如煙斗、大麻煙捲芯以及煙燒炭盆等癮君子的配備為特色的靜物畫。一般而言，畫中也經常會出現幾罐啤酒和幾杯酒。「煙草品」（tabakje）此一詞彙由荷蘭文翻譯過來的意思為「小煙草製品」。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar een type stilleven met rookgerei, zoals tabakspijpen, smeulende henneppitten en komforen met brandende kolen. Meestal zijn ook kruiken bier of glazen wijn afgebeeld.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bezieht sich auf einen Typus von Stillleben, das Raucherrequisiten zeigt, wie zum Beispiel Tabakspfeifen, glimmende Hanfdochte und Feuerschalen mit brennenden Kohlen. Bierkrüge und Weingläser sind üblicherweise ebenfalls dargestellt. Die Bezeichnung Tabakje bedeutet im Niederländischen "Kleiner Tabak".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
